Private.definition: intended for or restricted to the use of a particular person or group or class of persons

1 a.definition: intended for or restricted to the use of a particular person or group or class of personsnot available to the public [a park]

sub_terms.b: not related to, controlled by, or deriving from the state [a school]

2 a.definition: owned by or concerning an individual person or entity [ land]

sub_terms.b: not having shares that can be freely traded on the open market [a company]

3.definition: affecting the interests of a particular person, class or group of persons, or locality [ legislation] [ rights]

4 a.definition: not invested with or engaged in public office or employment [a citizen]

sub_terms.b: not related to or dependent on an official position [ correspondence]

5.definition: not known publicly or carried on in publicintended only for the persons involved
